data.title: Brian Wilson: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday
data.meta_description: Brian Wilson: Check out the list of all Brian Wilson movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest Brian Wilson news on Times of India.
data.text:
Today in the past: Interesting things that happened on May 16

etimes.in / May 16, 2024, 06:00 (IST)

Step into the annals of history on May 16th, a day pulsating with gripping stories and transformative moments. From audacious adventures to political upheavals, scientific revelations, and cultural landmarks, each event unfolds as a captivating chapter in humanity's grand saga. Get ready to be swept away by tales of resilience, ingenuity, and societal shifts that have etched their mark on the canvas of time.

Brian Wilson's team files petition for conservatorship after death of his wife

ANI / Feb 17, 2024, 12:06 (IST)

Brian Wilson's business manager LeeAnn Hard and his longtime manager and publicist Jean Sievers have filed a petition to become his conservators, managing his personal and medical decisions. The legal process involves Melinda Ledbetter, Los Angeles Superior Court, and the Associated Press. Wilson is currently undergoing treatment for dementia and has been diagnosed with a major neurocognitive disorder.

'Smile Please': Bijay Anand begins dubbing for his upcoming film

TNN / May 03, 2019, 13:36 (IST)

Indian cinema's veteran star, Bijay Anand made his debut in Marathi industry with the film 'Ye Re Ye Re Paisa' directed by Sanjay Jadhav. Bijay's impressive performance on the big screen had garnered lot accolades for his villainous role in the film.

Photo: Prasad Oak looks dapper in this sunkissed picture

TNN / Mar 07, 2019, 17:28 (IST)

Marathi cinema's actor-turned-director and producer has often thrown us off guard with his outlandish and quirky looks. The ‘Kaccha Limbu’ director knows exactly how to grab the limelight for all the right reasons. Well, he's done it yet again, this time the star has drawn attention for his uber cool avatar.

For at least a day, all the world is 'Margaritaville' in homage to Jimmy Buffett

AP / Sep 03, 2023, 03:47 (IST)

Fans around the world, including Key West and New York City, mourned the passing of singer Jimmy Buffett at 76. Buffett's hit song "Margaritaville" has become synonymous with Key West. Tributes poured in from President Joe Biden, former President Bill Clinton, Brian Wilson of the Beach Boys, and Paul McCartney. Fans gathered in New York City to reminisce and visited the Margaritaville restaurant in Times Square to celebrate Buffett's life.

Seymour Stein, record exec who signed up Madonna, dead at 80

AP / Apr 03, 2023, 07:59 (IST)

Seymour Stein, the founder of Sire Records, has died at age 80 in Los Angeles from cancer. Stein, who is in the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, gained his reputation by launching the careers of Madonna, Talking Heads, and many others. He demonstrated his deep knowledge of music in his signings of new wave bands, including the Ramones, Talking Heads, and the Pretenders.

Fortification wall at Old Goa faces threat as construction work encroaches on buffer zone

TNN / Jul 04, 2022, 04:10 (IST)

Construction activity near the centuries-old outer fortification wall encircling Old Goa city of yore has upset some heritage lovers, as promoters of a multi-dwelling complex have allegedly encroached into the old wall’s buffer zone shown in Regional Plan (RP) 2021. Old Goa’s boundaries, as a capital, lay a few miles away from the present limits. The fortification wall, which was extended in the 16th century by the Portuguese upon the old one built during the Adil Shahi era passed through Corlim, Banastarim, Carambolim, Bainguinim and other areas.

'Margaritaville' singer Jimmy Buffett, who turned beach-bum life into an empire, dies at 76

AP / Sep 02, 2023, 23:48 (IST)

Jimmy Buffett, the singer-songwriter known for his beach bum soft rock and the hit song "Margaritaville," has died at the age of 76. Buffett, who built a billion-dollar empire of restaurants, resorts, and frozen concoctions, passed away surrounded by his family, friends, music, and dogs. He popularized a carefree and escapist lifestyle through his music and brand, which included restaurants, resorts, and various merchandise.

Queen's jubilees chronicle changing times in Britain

AFP / Jun 02, 2022, 08:33 (IST)

Queen Elizabeth II celebrates her 70th year on the throne. The Platinum Jubilee is only the ninth such celebration by a British monarch since King George III in 1809. The Queen's Diamond Jubilee came in the same year that London hosted the Olympics and Paralympics - 2012. The June 2-5 celebrations saw a river pageant, beacons lit, a thanksgiving service and a pop concert.

Oscars 2022: Beyonce goes up against husband Jay-Z, Ariana Grande and Billie Eilish still in the running as Academy's shortlists unveiled

TNN & Agencies / Dec 22, 2021, 10:43 (IST)

Beyonce, Jay-Z and Ariana Grande are all in the running for the best original song Oscar, but French shock-fest 'Titane' did not make the shortlist for best foreign film, as the Academy unveiled its annual shortlists Tuesday ahead of the formal nominations.

McCartney marks 80th birthday with Springsteen, 60,000 pals

AP / Jun 18, 2022, 11:41 (IST)

Hard to think of a better way for Paul McCartney to celebrate his 80th birthday than by singing 'Glory Days' onstage with Bruce Springsteen or being serenaded by some 60,000 well-wishers.

Bono: Gallagher brothers are incredible

PTI / Sep 08, 2017, 12:19 (IST)

U2 frontman Bono said he has no hard feelings towards Liam Gallagher despite him slagging off his band and thinks he and his brother Noel are "incredible" musicians.
